# Railway Production Environment Variables Reference
# This file shows the environment variables needed for Railway deployment
# DO NOT commit actual secrets - set these in Railway dashboard

# =============================================================================
# RUNTIME ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (Set in Railway Dashboard → Variables)
# =============================================================================

# Application Environment
NODE_ENV=production

# Port (automatically set by Railway - do NOT override)
PORT=${{PORT}}

# Database Connection (Reference the Postgres service)
# In Railway: New Variable → Add Reference → Select "Postgres.DATABASE_URL"
DATABASE_URL=${{Postgres.DATABASE_URL}}

# CORS Configuration (automatically uses your Railway domain)
CLIENT_URL=https://${{RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}

# Security - Generate a strong random secret
# Generate with: openssl rand -base64 32
JWT_SECRET=your-super-secret-random-jwt-key-change-this

# Google Maps API Key (optional)
# Get from: https://console.cloud.google.com/google/maps-apis
GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=your-google-maps-api-key

# =============================================================================
# BUILD-TIME VARIABLES (Already configured in railway.json)
# =============================================================================
# These are set automatically via railway.json build args during Docker build
# DO NOT add these to runtime variables - they are build arguments!
#
# REACT_APP_API_URL=https://${{RAILWAY_PUBLIC_DOMAIN}}/api
# REACT_APP_GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=${{GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY}}

# =============================================================================
# DEPLOYMENT NOTES
# =============================================================================
# 1. Railway uses Docker build (configured in railway.json)
# 2. DATABASE_URL must reference the Postgres service, not a hardcoded URL
# 3. React environment variables are set during build time via build args
# 4. PORT is automatically assigned by Railway
# 5. Use strong, unique values for JWT_SECRET in production

# For detailed deployment instructions, see RAILWAY_DEPLOYMENT.md
